The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

Life

 Social Register

 Stone splendour 

 What: 

 Exhibition of Noorjehan, Mumbai-based jewellery designer 

 Roopa Vohras latest line. 

 Where: Oriental Hall, Taj 

 Bengal. 

 When: September 2 and 3. 

 Take a look: Lots of rubies, 

 emeralds, blue and yellow topazes, pink and orange sapphiresNoorjehan 

 plays with an extended colour palette. The thrust is mainly 

 on the seasons hot favourites earrings and bracelets 

 boasting her signature Mughal style. 

 Roopa will display close to 300 

 pairs of earrings everything from dainty studs to shoulder-dusters. 

 Versatile and individualistic in terms of both 

 design and styling, these earrings are detachable and boast 

 colour-changing options. The bracelets, very cuff-like, 

 come in various finishes. 

 Pocket pinch: The prices 

 begin at Rs 7,000. The heavier, couture pieces are tagged 

 at Rs 20,000-plus. 

 Voiceover: It is 

 always great coming back to Calcutta because the response 

 is terrific. People here are well exposed to art and hence 

 appreciate and understand finer details, said Roopa, 

 whose client list boasts many a Bollywood beauty.




